<P><HI>Labadie (John de)</HI> a noted Teacher in <HI>Holland,</HI> 535.</P>
<P><HI>Lambert</HI> (Major-General) di&s;&s;uades <HI>Cromwel</HI> from a&s;&s;uming the Crown, for which he is made to re&s;ign his Commi&s;&s;ion, 159. Is &s;ent General by the Parliament again&s;t Sir <HI>George Booth,</HI> whom he de|feats, 206. He is tried and condemned, but ob|tains his Life, and is confin'd to a &s;mall I&s;land near <HI>Plymouth,</HI> 317.</P>
<P><HI>Lampit (William)</HI> Prie&s;t at <HI>Ulver&s;tone,</HI> oppo&s;ed by <HI>G. Fox,</HI> 55. And put to Silence by him, 57. Friends barbarou&s;ly abu&s;ed by his Hearers, 59. He with another Prie&s;t are &s;ilent upon the entring of <HI>Miles Halhead</HI> into the Hou&s;e where he was preaching, 71, 71. His Death, 511.</P>
